OL,3,CEngland fans embracing Texas culture
OL,4,Cas Three Lions prepare for World Cup
OL,5,Copener
OL,7,FEngland fans have said they are
OL,8,Fembracing Texas culture as they bought
OL,9,Fcowboy hats and boots ahead of the
OL,10,FThree Lions' World Cup opener.
OL,12,FSupporters gathered in Dallas Fort
OL,13,FWorth on Monday to soak up the
OL,14,Fatmosphere two days before England's
OL,15,Fgame against Croatia at the AT&T
OL,16,FStadium in nearby Arlington.
OL,18,FRussell, from Stoke-on-Trent, proudly
OL,19,Fshowed off his new cowboy outfit and
OL,20,Fjoked he would now have to wear it
OL,21,Fevery day.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1781581669
OL,3,CEngland fans embracing Texas culture
OL,4,Cas Three Lions prepare for World Cup
OL,5,Copener
OL,7,F"We've got into the Texas spirit," he
OL,8,Ftold the Press Association.
OL,10,F"But I've got to wear this every day
OL,11,Fnow, haven't I?"
OL,13,FHis friend Mitch laughed: "They
OL,14,Fhaven't bought them here, they've
OL,15,Fbrought them over from Stoke."
OL,17,FRussell replied: "They're not coming
OL,18,Foff these aren't."
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@bO]rD@AOUsD@PO]uD@[OUwD@^O]yD@
OL,26,AROUzD@RO]
